        <h2>About This Tool</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Purpose:</strong> This tool provides an interactive way to explore medical procedure charges specific to 
            <em>Nationwide Children's Hospital</em>. Users can search by CPT codes, compare standard and negotiated charges, 
            and filter by payer or plan type.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Data Source:</strong> The pricing data is sourced directly from publicly available hospital charge datasets. 
            While we strive for accuracy, all values are for informational purposes only and may not reflect real-time billing rates.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Intended Users:</strong> This tool is designed for patients, families, and healthcare professionals who 
            want to better understand typical charges for medical procedures at Nationwide Children's Hospital.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Using the Data:</strong> Use this tool to identify general cost ranges, compare charges between procedures, 
            and explore how negotiated rates vary by payer. This is not a substitute for professional billing advice.
        </p>
